    <!-- How to Record -->
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-plus-circle"></i> Recording Transactions</h2>
        
        <h3>Method 1: Quick Add (Fastest)</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Press <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>N</kbd> or click the Quick Add button</li>
            <li>Select Income or Expense</li>
            <li>Enter amount, description, and category</li>
            <li>Click Save</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="help-note-inline">
            <i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Quick Add is great for simple transactions. Use Full Form for detailed entries.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Method 2: Full Transaction Form</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to <strong>Transactions</strong></li>
            <li>Click <strong>Add Transaction</strong></li>
            <li>Fill in all required and optional fields</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Save Transaction</strong></li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Split Transactions -->
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-code-branch"></i> Split Transactions</h2>
        <p>
            Sometimes one payment covers multiple categories. For example, a $500 check might 
            cover $300 for equipment and $200 for training supplies.
        </p>
        
        <div class="help-example">
            <h4>Example Split Transaction:</h4>
            <table class="help-table">
                <tr>
                    <th>Total Amount</th>
                    <td colspan="2">$500.00</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <th>Split 1</th>
                    <td>Equipment & Supplies</td>
                    <td>$300.00</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <th>Split 2</th>
                    <td>Training Materials</td>
                    <td>$200.00</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>
        
        <h4>How to Create a Split:</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>In the transaction form, enable "Split Transaction"</li>
            <li>Add each category and amount</li>
            <li>Ensure splits total to the transaction amount</li>
            <li>Save</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Linking to Donors/Grants -->
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Linking Transactions</h2>
        
        <h3>Linking to a Donor</h3>
        <p>When recording a donation, link it to the donor to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Automatically update their giving history</li>
            <li>Generate year-end tax receipts</li>
            <li>Track donor retention metrics</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Linking to a Grant</h3>
        <p>When spending grant funds, link the expense to the grant to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Track grant spending vs. award amount</li>
            <li>Ensure compliance with grant restrictions</li>
            <li>Generate grant expense reports</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="help-warning">
            <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
            <strong>Important:</strong> Always link grant expenses! This is critical for grant reporting and compliance.
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Filtering & Searching -->
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2><i class="fas fa-filter"></i> Finding Transactions</h2>
        
        <h3>Filter Options:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Date Range</strong> - Show transactions within a period</li>
            <li><strong>Type</strong> - Income, Expense, or Transfer only</li>
            <li><strong>Category</strong> - Filter by category</li>
            <li><strong>Account</strong> - Show only one account's transactions</li>
            <li><strong>Search</strong> - Search descriptions, payees, tags</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Quick Search Tips:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Press <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>F</kbd> for global search</li>
            <li>Search by payee name: "Fire Equipment"</li>
            <li>Search by PO number: "PO-2024"</li>
            <li>Search by description: "training hose"</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
